# 🏠 Cisco Packet Tracer – Home Network Simulation

## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates the setup and configuration of a basic home network using Cisco Packet Tracer. The network includes:
- 1 Router (1941)
- 2 Switches (2960-24TT)
- 4 PCs (PC0–PC3) across two subnets
- Static IP configuration
- Successful ping tests verifying connectivity across the network

---

## 🗺️ Network Topology
![Full Network Topology](images/PotentialSetupComplete.PNG)

- **LAN 1 (Left Side):**
  - PC0: `192.168.1.10`
  - PC1: `192.168.1.11`
  - Default Gateway: `192.168.1.1`

- **LAN 2 (Right Side):**
  - PC2: `192.168.2.10`
  - PC3: `192.168.2.11`
  - Default Gateway: `192.168.2.1`

Router interfaces:
- `GigabitEthernet0/0`: `192.168.1.1` (to Switch0)
- `GigabitEthernet0/1`: `192.168.2.1` (to Switch1)

---

## ⚙️ Configuration Steps

### 🔧 Router CLI
```bash
enable
configure terminal
interface gig0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
exit

interface gig0/1
ip address 192.168.2.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown
exit
